  <summary>6/12/2006--Introduced.
Cherry Valley National Wildlife Refuge Study Act - Requires the Secretary of the Interior to conduct a study to evaluate specified fish and wildlife habitat and aquatic and terrestrial communities in northeastern Pennsylvania for potential acquisition and subsequent inclusion in a future Cherry Valley National Wildlife Refuge. Prohibits the Secretary from acquiring more than 30,000 total acres of land, water, and interests in the study area.</summary>
